description:
Creates an issue in a GitHub repository. Requires a valid GitHub token with repo write permissions. Rate limited to 5000 requests/hour per token. Use this when you need to track a bug, feature request, or task in a specific repository.

Example: create_github_issue(owner='anthropics', repo='anthropic-sdk-python', title='Bug: streaming fails on timeout', body='Detailed description...', labels=['bug']) → {'id': 1234, 'url': 'https://github.com/...'}

Fails with 404 if repo does not exist or token lacks permissions.
